<para>
  While <link linkend="Section-Concepts-Mesh-Solving">solving</link> a
  time dependent problem, a <classname>MeshFileOutput</classname> can
  be <link linkend="Section-Tasks-ScheduledOutput">scheduled</link> to
  save all of the mesh data at intermediate times.  The resulting file
  can be reloaded into &oof2; by <xref
  linkend="MenuItem-OOF.File.Load.Data"/> or via the <link
  linkend="Section-Running"><userinput>--data</userinput></link>
  startup command line option.
</para>
<para>
  The output file will contain the complete definition of the &mesh;.
  It will contain a single copy of all of the &micro;, &skel;, and
  &mesh; structural data, as well as the &field; values at the
  scheduled output times.
</para>
<para>
  The only type of <xref linkend="RegisteredClass-OutputDestination"/>
  that can be used with <classname>MeshFileOutput</classname> is <xref
  linkend="RegisteredClass-DataFileOutput"/>.
</para>


